 What went into transforming Victoria Island or Lekki is a combination of the efforts of past and present leaders in introducing developmental projects. The Olofin Adimula of Ado Odo, Ogun State, Oba Abdul Lateef Adeniran Akanni, is on the right path too, as he is not leaving any stone unturned to ensure the development of his kingdom. The sprawling town of Ado Odo will come alive today as there will be a foundation-laying ceremony of his ultra-modern estate in Ogun State Housing Corporation, Oke-Oyinbo. The celebration is expected to be grand affair which will attract royal fathers, top politicians, well-wishers and top government functionaries.